description: Who is Supergirl? Kara Danvers has learned a lot about her super-abilities, her strengths as a friend and as a sister, her love of being human and alien at the same time. And now she’ll need to pull it all together to defeat her most dangerous foe to date!
name: End Games Chapter 12

description: Will Spider-Man's Brand New Day be ruined by foes old or new - or a combination of the two? First, Spidey must survive Kraven's First Hunt - but this isn't the Kravinoff he knew. In fact, she might be even more lethal! Then, Spidey will face a Norman Osborn who has changed, too - because this time, Osborn has the force of the law behind him. And Osborn's dark version of order is maintained by the twisted Thunderbolts! Another classic foe, Hammerhead, has been revived by Spidey's newest nemesis, the nihilistic Mister Negative. The two unite in a rampage of crime - but as the bullets fly, the Punisher joins the fray! Plus: Jackpot faces a Skrull Secret Invasion! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #565-577, AMAZING SPIDER-MAN ANNUAL (2008) #1, SECRET INVASION: AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #1-3 and material from AMAZING SPIDER-MAN: EXTRA! #1.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: The Amazing Spider-Man: Brand New Day: The Complete Collection

description: Zzzax and the Super-Adaptoid strike! But as the action heats up...it may take more than the assembled Avengers to safely win the day! Don't miss part two of this 4-part exclusive saga presented by Western Union.
name: Part 2: Double Trouble

description:
In a future version of Earth, there is a city grown so chaotically massive that its inhabitants no longer recall what "land" is. Within this megastructure the silent, stoic Kyrii is on a mission to find the Net Terminal Gene—a genetic mutation that once allowed humans to access the cybernetic NetSphere. Armed with a powerful Graviton Beam Emitter, Kyrii fends off waves of attacks from fellow humans, cyborgs and silicon-based lifeforms. Along the way, he encounters a highly-skilled scientist whose body has deteriorated from a lengthy imprisonment who promises to help Kyrii find the Net Terminal Gene, once she settles a score for herself...

Contents

  • LOG.1: Net Terminal Gene
  • LOG.2: The Memory of Land
  • LOG.3: Technomads
  • EX-LOG
  • LOG.4: The Administration
  • LOG.5: Escape
  • LOG.6: Silicon Life
  • LOG.7: The Builders
  • EX-LOG: Abandoned Nest
  • LOG.8: The Cluster
  • LOG.9: Bio-Electric, Inc.

Chris Vargas is a middle-aged man with a hacking cough, an obsolete job, and a bombastic secret: whenever he likes, he can transform into the teenage superhero CAPTAIN KID! In this, his first recorded adventure, he encounters Helea, a mystery woman who knows more about him than he does, and Halliday, a mad businessman with a catastrophic weapon!

Officer Rick Murphy just wanted revenge on the men who killed his pregnant fiancée and with the power of Death Force he thought it would be easy. But now, framed for murder and on the run it’s a race to see who gets to kill him first… the Japanese mob or the entire Philadelphia police force.

Plus, learn the final fate of the Brotherhood of Dada and witness the rise of the unstoppable Candlemaker!
name: Book Two

description:
...And the door will open, part 5

Arthur explains to Lilia that he and Sasha are the members of the Bookwizard Order, guarding the thin line between reality and literary fiction. And all mysterious creatures Lilia met are characters from books, who somehow appeared in our world, and died here. But Arthur's passionate is blatantly interrupted, when our heroes literally sank through the floor into a huge library, where they meet a mysterious woman.
name: ...And the door will open Part 5

description: In the rubble of the once great city, Bones encounters Quantrai and their mortal combat comes to a final conclusion as Bones has nothing left to lose. On a mission to fulfill the prophecy at any cost, Dorvalus succumbs to the will of his master but it may be too late.

The saga continues! After the events of volume one, Elanor has found herself on both sides of fame; as hero and as Hellion. Omega tries to secretly recover from the loss of the Radix and the future of The Hex is uncertain. Osrick is caught off guard as Elanor meets an unlikely friend...

Since the rise of the Regime, The Flash has always been one of Superman’s most tenuous allies. Now his loyalty is really going to be tested, as someone he loves has to face Superman’s unswerving justice. Then, with the Speedster at his most vulnerable, Batman offers him a risky way out.

volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Five

description:
After a mission of vengeance in Helsinki, James Bond returns to London and assumes the workload of a fallen 00 Section agent. His new mission takes him to Berlin, presumably to break up an agile drug-trafficking operation. But Bond has no idea of the forces gathered in secret against him, the full scope of an operation that's much scarier and more lethal than he could possibly imagine. Berlin is about to catch fire... and James Bond is trapped inside. Dynamite Entertainment proudly presents VARGR, the debut storyline in the all-new James Bond comic book series, as crafted by masterful writer Warren Ellis (Transmetropolitan, The Authority) and artist Jason Masters (Batman Incorporated, Guardians of the Galaxy).

In this issue: Judge Dredd: Dust to Dust by Michael Carroll, Henry Flint, and Annie Parkhouse; Realm of the Damned by Alec Worley, Pye Parr, and Luke Preece; Lawless: Of Munce and Men by Dan Abnett, Phil Winslade and Ellie De Ville, Blunt by TC Eglington, Boo Cook, and Simon Bowland. Plus fiction ‘No Act of Kindness’ by Steve Frame and features on Joe Hill by Stephen Jewell and Predator vs Judge Dredd vs Aliens by Karl Stock. And don’t forget the bagged graphic novel: Sinister Dexter: Junk Bond by Dan Abnett, Frazer Irving, Andy Clarke, Simon Davis, Gary Caldwell, Ellie De Ville!

description:
The first arc of KILLBOX ends here! Reeling from the new information Father Michael has given them, Tim and Emi attempt an escape only to be confronted by Sasha Rate, a handguns expert who likes to shoot first and ask questions later. But Emi and Timothy need her help if they're going to dismantle the Killbox from the inside -- that is, if the game's demonic contractors don't do it first.

Note: The digital edition (7/20/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Angel's father stirs up a hornets nest of trouble when he declares war on a rival criminal faction who harbor a powerful Dhizhi of ther own. Gangsters, Triad, Cops, and monsters all collide in a spectacular showdown that will have permanent repercussions!

The only thing Masaru wants to do in life is to help people and dreams of becoming a caregiver one day. He desperately needs an internship and is soon interning at a clinic run by Director Koharu. He can’t help feeling an instant attraction to her, but soon discovers that she runs an unorthodox practice known as Sexual Neurology. He finds himself “helping” the female clients with their sexual problems.

Masaru reluctantly accepts his mission to help all the women with broken hearts that enters Koharu’s clinic, but he finds it increasingly difficult to do so when all he wants is to have Koharu all to himself.

Case.1 - Case.10.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The erotic exploits of Director Koharu, Hane, and Masaru continues in volume 2 of Love Clinic. The notoriety of the clinic is growing thanks in large part to the success of Masaru curing patients of their sexual inhibitions. Although, his progress with deepening his relationship with Koharu...not so much. Opportunities to confess his feelings seem to constantly pass him by. Determined, Masaru builds confidence day by day to finally tell her how he feels, but time isn't on his side. The time to say goodbye is drawing closer as his internship at the clinic will soon come to an end...

Case.11 - Case.19.
name: Vol. 2

description:
The Madballs have made it to the biggest, wackiest intergalactic sporting event—the Bizzaro Bowl! They're facing down their nemesis, the headless Torsoids, who've tried everything to keep them out of the match. Screamin' Meemie and Horn Head have totally different ideas on how to lead the team to victory, but it'll take everything they've got to beat the Torsoids' superior size, not to mention their arms and legs!

It’s not so easy being Grace… cast out among misfits, toppled from her position as the ultimate Queen Bee, and now forced to consider that maybe she's got more in common with Norman than she thought. Maybe, just maybe... she's a horrifying monster who has no place in civilized society?

While protecting her Overwatch squad as they rescue hostages from a Talon stronghold, sniper Ana Amari faces off against an unforeseen foe—a shooter who’s as good as she is. Ana must use all her wiles to get her people out of harm’s way, but at what cost?
name: Ana Amari: Legacy

description: The Strategic Defense Initiative (SDI) is hot on the trail of the Tesla-1 device after a deadly encounter on the streets of Hollywood. Meanwhile, Matthew learns why his father wasn’t involved with his upbringing and finally gets to bond with him before this issue’s stunning conclusion.

In search of the Holy Grail, part 4

The "ICA" team manages to get to the tower of Bismarck before the enemy, and Nika, showing the wonders of ingenuity and dexterity, seizes the clue for finding the Grail. But then the enemy group headed by Helga Lemke shows up, and Nika, along with the clue, falls into the hands of the "Black Moon" fanatics...
name: In Search of the Holy Grail Part 4

description: 2215, the planet of Caldoria saw its population exterminated by an experimental Artificial Intelligence. Among the rare few survivors, Stan, a young boy, who has been living in isolation for over a year, discovers an industrial robot that strangely does not seem to obey the A.I. Accepting it as a friend, Stan nicknames it "Rocky", and together, they go searching for possible survivors...
name: Vol. 1

description: Rosalind sets out to avenge the death of her father but makes a mistake that could be fatal for her and the creature in the Shadow Glass.
name: Chapter Five: The Devil's Bellowes

description: Outmanned, outgunned, out of time and out of luck The Six'll need a miracle to survive this one. Miracles don't come cheap - and neither does freedom. The adage goes, "freedom isn't free," but The Six just didn't know the cost could be so damn high and it's going to take every prayer in the Good Book for McQuade and the boys to keep Sara and Shaun alive. And for them to do that the trick is they have to keep on breathing too. With the Cartel tightening their grip and closing in every second that's going to be one motherf'n tough trick to pull off.

Scottish-born Rossi Gifford's quarterly tale continues in what David Gibbons calls 'dynamic and involving with a gorgeous colour palette.' Adventure and danger lie ahead as Freya and Skoll travel deeper into the forest.

Note: The digital edition (7/20/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

In sports manga, there's no "I" in team! Sports manga are about more than just the game—they're a showcase for the real, deep and sometimes unbelievable characters that create the makeup of every great team. The Sports Manga Essentials include a huge lineup of our favorites including Haikyu!!, Kuroko's Basketball, The Prince of Tennis and Cross Manage. Each story offers a different look into the world's of these sporting teams, that goes beyond just "sport". So, enjoy this collection of sports manga, and remember that the only "I" on this sports manga team is you!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Into the Inferno!

We rejoin our heroes on the eve of a terrible calamity that threatens not only the city of Cosmopolis, but all of existence. Do they have what it takes to brave terrifying, new worlds to save their own?!
name: Into the Inferno!

description: It comes full circle. Frank and Evelyn return to the diner to meet with her father and resolve things once and for all.
name: Chapter Seven: I Won't Kill Him

description: Zen Intergalactic Ninja is one of the rare independent titles with more than 100 comic books to date, and its fan base tells us it's better than ever. In The Zenith Orb a fist sized jewel becomes a fist full of trouble. Marooned on an uncharted planet, Zen encounters Notan the Magnificent for the first time, makes new allies, and a few new enemies. Written and with gorgeous full color art by Zen co-creator Dan Coté, this kid-friendly original graphic novel has enough eye candy and sophisticated turns to entertain readers of all ages.
name: GN

Also: to save Tony Stark, it's Iron Man versus Iron Man!

A 'Secret Wars' chapter! The Silver Surfer is tasked with the greatest challenge imaginable: rebuild the entire universe! By Dan Slott and Michael Allred!

description:
It’s time for another titanic team-up, as Cloak and Dagger join forces with the wise-crackin' wall-crawler to battle the Absorbing Man! Use your powers to fix the balance between light and dark, and take a spin across the strands of the Spider-Verse! This issue’s Web Warrior is the spooky Spider-Man Noir! Who is this time-travelling hero – and what connection does he have to Peter Parker?

All this and more in the next exciting issue of… Ultimate Spider-Man magazine!

Think squirrels are harmless little fur balls that live in trees? Well think again! Those critters can be pretty tough when they need to be, as the Wizard will hopefully find out when he takes on Spidey and Squirrel Girl in this issue's totally nuts comic strip!

Plus, there's a super-sized dose of girl power with our Spider-Girl fact file and puzzles, and a totally amazing looking collectible Iron Spider poster that you can web to your wall!

It’s show time!

The master manipulator Mysterio strikes this month – will the wall-crawler’s spider-senses be enough to tackle the covert crook?!

Team up with Iron Fist and see if your combined might can contend with the sinister Scorpion!

Ultimate Spider-Man #290 – Jam-packed with puzzles, activities and games, spider-fans would be mad to miss it!
Many of the stories are Christmas themed
